<topic template="Default" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../helpproject.xsd">
  <title translate="true">Idea Space Cards</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">Idea Space Cards</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><image src="IdeaSpaceCardTools.png" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"></image></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Each Idea Space card is given its own mini-toolbar at top right. This allows you to perform various operations on the card itself rather than the tool that the card displays. From left to right, the operations are:</text></para>
    <list id="1" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Normal" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:9pt; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">Go Back</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> to the previous card. A history list of cards visited is kept. This button allows you to go back to the previously selected card in this list.</text></li>
      <li styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">Go Forward</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> to the next card in the history list. Obviously, this option is only available if you have previously use the </text><text styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">Go Back</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> button.</text></li>
      <li styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">Move Left</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">, moves the current card&apos;s tab to the left.</text></li>
      <li styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">Move Right</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">, moved the current card&apos;s tab to the right.</text></li>
      <li styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">Close Card</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">, closes the current card. If there are any unsaved changes you will be prompted before the card is closed.</text></li>
    </list>
  </body>
</topic>
